diff --git a/docs/CONTROL_API.md b/docs/CONTROL_API.md
index c32ad55..ecd0dbe 100644
--- a/docs/CONTROL_API.md
+++ b/docs/CONTROL_API.md
@@ -246,3 +246,15 @@ without terminal decoration and works without a TTY. Exit codes distinguish
 usage, authorization, compatibility, revision conflict, connection, and generic
 failures. Mutations are not retried unless the same idempotency key and payload
 are retained, and client/server incompatibility fails before dispatch.
+
+## Read-only Bubble Tea TUI
+
+Run `ya tui` to open the keyboard-only terminal client. It provides connection,
+overview, providers, accounts, models, configuration, operations, and lifecycle
+event screens. `Tab`/arrow keys or number keys switch screens, `r` reconnects,
+`t` cycles auto/light/dark/monochrome, and `q` exits only the client.
+
+Every state includes a text label; color is never the sole status signal. The
+TUI renders sanitized Control API errors with request IDs, does not write logs
+into the controlled terminal, and periodically reconnects without cancelling
+daemon operations.
diff --git a/docs/qa/ya-tui-10.md b/docs/qa/ya-tui-10.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..e42b961
--- /dev/null
+++ b/docs/qa/ya-tui-10.md
@@ -0,0 +1,7 @@
+# YA-TUI-10 acceptance evidence
+
+- Full keyboard navigation and explicit text status labels; monochrome rendering has no ANSI color escapes.
+- Golden render tests cover compact, standard, and wide terminal classes.
+- Offline/reconnect and sanitized request-ID diagnostics are tested.
+- Quitting the TUI emits no operation cancellation or daemon lifecycle call.
+- Bubble Tea, Bubbles, and Lip Gloss are pinned to Go 1.22-compatible releases.
